<p><b>Gordie Sampson</b> (born July 30, 1971) is a Grammy award-winning <a href="Canada" title="Canada">Canadian</a> <a href="Singer" title="Singer" class="mw-redirect">singer</a>-<a href="Songwriter" title="Songwriter">songwriter</a> and <a href="Record_producer" title="Record producer">producer</a> from <a href="Big_Pond,_Nova_Scotia" title="Big Pond, Nova Scotia">Big Pond, Nova Scotia</a>.</p>
<p>He has written songs for <a href="Carrie_Underwood" title="Carrie Underwood">Carrie Underwood</a> ("Jesus, Take the Wheel", "Just A Dream", "Get Out Of This Town"), <a href="Martina_McBride" title="Martina McBride">Martina McBride</a> ("If I Had Your Name", "You're Not Leavin Me"), <a href="LeAnn_Rimes" title="LeAnn Rimes">LeAnn Rimes</a> ("Long Night", "Save Myself"), <a href="Miranda_Lambert" title="Miranda Lambert">Miranda Lambert</a> ("Better In The Long Run"), Rascal Flatts ("Let It Hurt", "Great Big Love"), Hunter Hayes ("Storm Warning"), Eden's Edge ("Too Good To Be True"), and <a href="George_Canyon" title="George Canyon">George Canyon</a> ("My Name"); and produced and sound engineered for <a href="Damhnait_Doyle" title="Damhnait Doyle">Damhnait Doyle</a>, <a href="Natalie_MacMaster" title="Natalie MacMaster">Natalie MacMaster</a>, <a href="The_Cottars" title="The Cottars">The Cottars</a>, <a href="Bruce_Guthro" title="Bruce Guthro">Bruce Guthro</a>, and <a href="Buddy_MacMaster" title="Buddy MacMaster">Buddy MacMaster</a>.</p>
